casebody.data:
People ex rel. McQuien, Appellant, v. Theatrical Mechanical Ass’n, Respondent. (Supreme Court, General Term, First Department. March 14, 1890.)

Argued before Van Brunt, P. J., and Brady and Daniels, JJ.

Smith Tuttle, for appellant. Howe & Hummel, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion will not be considered under this order to show cause. See 8 N. Y. Supp. 675.
